4-H’ers Are to Feature Former Leaders March is Wisconsin 4-H folk will hoar about their state pioneer leaders when they tune in on “The 4-H Club of the Air” over state stations WHA-WLBL Sat- unlay noon, March 18, at 12:46. Miss Elisabeth Annoy. Polk county girl who served from 1917 to 1920, and the first woman to serve on the state staff; Kail Cooper, Grant county boy. who is the first men added to the state staff, served from 1917 to 1982; E. A. Stnkdyk, Door county 4-H boy, who served as assistant state club leader during 1922 and 1823; Mildred Hager by Gabbard, Dunn county 4-H girl, a of the state staff from 1921 to 1924; and Elisabeth Salter Eby, Marathon county girl, who served as assistant state leader from 1924 to 1934, are among those to be featured. (First pub. Feb. 16; last March 23.)
